Merge pull request #5 from mozilla/raw-sql-backend

Add a RAW SQL backend (bug 927794)

Change the way celery bootstraps.

Attach the pyramid registry to the celery app in the pyramid bootstrap, and not in the celery bootstrap itself.

This allows to run the tests with celery_always_eager set to true to be sure everythign is working the right way.

Use konfig to read the documentation.

And also make the tasks access to the pyramid registry (so that they can access
the backend they need to work)
Try to access the registry from the celery task.

- The PRD says we should return "id", not "addon-id" or "addonid".
- We had an ugly pdb here.

some tests coverage to test everything is working the way it should

Bootstrap the cornice webapp.

It's pluggable so it's possible to change the backend to use directly from the
configuration file. This is made to allow easy configuration in the future.

The default implementation will probably be the RAW SQL since that's a small
project. In the future, we could do some more complex stuff, like using caching
strategies.

Update the setup.py file.
